<paragraph id="99313682FA72D421FF565C0FA819FAEC" blockId="4.[166,1225,647,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
B i o n o m i c s. Larva feeds within the midrib, with short offshoots into the leaf blade. Pupation takes place inside of the leaf in the base of the midrib (
<bibRefCitation id="FD1F4B73FA72D421FC195C6FA86DFAEC" author="Spencer, K. A. The" box="[916,1086,1351,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" refId="ref13567" refString="Spencer, K. A. The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark - Klampenborg: Scandinavian Sci. Press, 1976. - Part 1. - 304 p." type="book" year="1976">Spencer, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
